cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SL, cs.SDQ 

The paper deals with improving the performance of automatic speech recognition (ASR) using a deep neural network (DNN) in a multi-microphone configuration. This involves processing audio signals, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SD (Sound). The paper also mentions the use of attention mechanisms, which is a common technique in natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of a DNN also suggests the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with ASR performance measures, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SL (Speech and Language Processing). Finally, the paper proposes a new framework for ASR, which could potentially fall under the sub-category of cs.SDQ (Sound and Music Computing).
